## üîß Gestion Version WordPress

### Configuration Variable d'Environnement

La version de l'image WordPress est maintenant d√©finie dans **`docker/.env`** :

```bash
# docker/.env
WORDPRESS_IMAGE_VERSION=php8.3-apache
```

### Versions Disponibles

| Version | Description | Recommandation |
|---------|-------------|----------------|
| `php8.3-apache` | **PHP 8.3** + Apache (stable) | ‚úÖ **Recommand√©** |
| `php8.4-apache` | PHP 8.4 + Apache (r√©cent) | ‚ö†Ô∏è Tester avant |
| `latest` | Derni√®re version | ‚ùå **Non recommand√©** (impr√©visible) |
| `6.4-php8.3-apache` | WordPress 6.4 + PHP 8.3 | ‚úÖ Version fixe |
| `6.5-php8.3-apache` | WordPress 6.5 + PHP 8.3 | ‚úÖ Version fixe |

**üéØ Recommandation** : Utiliser `phpX.X-apache` (version PHP fixe) plut√¥t que `latest`

### Mettre √† Jour la Version WordPress

```bash
# 1. Backup pr√©ventif
make wordpress_backup

# 2. √âditer docker/.env
nano docker/.env

# Changer :
# WORDPRESS_IMAGE_VERSION=php8.3-apache
# En :
WORDPRESS_IMAGE_VERSION=php8.4-apache

# 3. Red√©marrer les conteneurs
make dev_down
make dev_up

# ou rebuild si changement majeur
make dev_rebuild
```

